CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper September 21, 1946, pg. 16, reads: "Dilettantes Entertain Local Celebrities - The Dilettantes, an interracial group interested in cultural development, entertained a delegation of visitors at their meeting held at the Centre Avenue Branch YMCA Friday evening, Sept. 13. Top picture shows Jay Looney, author; Arthor [Arthur] Lewis, May-Stern personnel director; Mrs. Mildred Thorne Evanson, dramatic teacher; Mrs. Abraham Lincoln, civic leader; Dorothy Scott and Carl Christian, representatives of the Dilettantes... - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Jay Looney, Arthur Lewis, Mildred Thorne Evanson, Mrs. Abraham Lincoln, Dorothy Scott, and Carl Christian gathered for Dilettantes group program in Centre Avenue YMCA with Henry O. Tanner painting "Christ and His Mother" on wall
